## 4. Feature Specifications

### 4.1 Reel Saving via Share Sheet

**Description**: Users save a Reel directly from Instagram using the native OS share sheet. No copy-pasting, no switching apps manually.

**User Flow**:

1. User views a Reel on Instagram
2. Taps the **Share** icon on the Reel
3. Selects **ReelMind** from the share sheet
4. A bottom sheet appears in ReelMind showing: *"Saving reel... this will take a moment"*
5. User can dismiss and continue browsing — processing happens in the background
6. A push notification confirms: *"✅ Reel saved to [Category Name]"* or prompts for category if uncertain

**Technical Notes**:

- ReelMind registers as a share target for URLs on both iOS (Share Extension) and Android (Intent Filter)
- The shared data is the public Instagram Reel URL (e.g., `https://www.instagram.com/reel/XXXXX/`)
- MVP supports **public account Reels only**

**Constraints**:

- Private account Reels are not supported in MVP (user sees a friendly error: *"This Reel is from a private account and can't be saved yet"*)
- Region-blocked or deleted Reels show an error with a retry option

---

### 4.2 AI Processing Pipeline (Backend — Triggered at Save Time)

> All heavy AI processing happens at **save time**, not at query time. This ensures sub-second query responses.
> 

**Step-by-step pipeline**:

```
URL Received
    ↓
Validate URL (public reel check)
    ↓
Download Reel (yt-dlp + FFmpeg — video + audio merged as .mp4)
    ↓
Extract Audio Track (FFmpeg — strip audio from .mp4)
    ↓
Fetch Page Metadata (caption, hashtags, creator handle, thumbnail)
    ↓
Audio Transcription
(OpenAI Whisper API — converts audio to text)
    ↓
Content Extraction
(LLM prompt: extract products mentioned, topics discussed, key advice given)
    ↓
Auto-Categorization
(LLM prompt: assign to best-fit category with confidence score)
    ↓
[If confidence ≥ threshold] → Auto-assign + notify user
[If confidence < threshold] → Send notification asking user to name category
    ↓
Generate Vector Embeddings
(text-embedding-3-small or equivalent)
    ↓
Store in Vector DB + Relational DB
Cleanup temporary media files from server
```

**Confidence Threshold**: 75% (tunable). Below this, a notification is triggered.

> [!IMPORTANT]
yt-dlp is an open-source tool that works by reverse-engineering Instagram's CDN URLs from public page responses. It does not use Instagram's official API. It must be kept updated on the server (`yt-dlp -U`) as Instagram periodically changes its response structure. This is the same mechanism used by all reel downloader websites.
> 

**Content stored per Reel**:

- Original URL
- Reel thumbnail (cached)
- Creator handle & display name
- Full transcription
- AI-extracted summary (2–3 sentences)
- Products/topics mentioned (structured list)
- Category assigned
- Vector embedding
- Timestamp saved
- Processing status (queued / processing / done / failed)

