## 5. Technical Architecture

### 5.1 Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Rationale |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Mobile App** | React Native + Expo | Cross-platform iOS + Android, JS ecosystem, Expo handles share extensions & push notifications |
| **Backend API** | Node.js + Express (or Fastify) | Same language as frontend, fast async processing |
| **Task Queue** | BullMQ + Redis | Async AI processing pipeline — jobs don't block the API |
| **Reel Extraction** | yt-dlp + FFmpeg (server-side) | yt-dlp downloads public Reels (video+audio) from Instagram's CDN; FFmpeg merges/extracts audio stream |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL (via Supabase) | Relational data: users, reels, categories, metadata |
| **Vector Database** | Supabase pgvector | RAG embeddings stored alongside relational data — simpler ops than Pinecone for MVP |
| **Audio Transcription** | OpenAI Whisper API | Best-in-class accuracy, handles multiple languages and accents |
| **LLM (Categorization + Chat)** | GPT-4o (OpenAI) | Strong reasoning, function calling support, large context window |
| **Embeddings** | OpenAI text-embedding-3-small | Cost-efficient, high quality for semantic search |
| **Push Notifications** | Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) + Expo Push | Handles both iOS (APNs) and Android, inline reply support |
| **Auth** | Supabase Auth | Email/social login, JWT, Row Level Security out of the box |
| **Storage** | Supabase Storage | Reel thumbnails only (video files deleted after transcription to save cost) |
| **Hosting** | Railway or Render | Simple Node.js deployment with Redis + yt-dlp/FFmpeg support |

### 5.2 High-Level Architecture Diagram

```
[Instagram App]
      |
   Share Sheet (user shares Reel URL)
      |
[ReelMind Mobile App] ──── Auth ────► [Supabase Auth]
      |
   HTTP POST /reels/save (URL + user_id)
      |
[Node.js API] → validates URL → Enqueue job
      |
   [Redis / BullMQ Queue]
      |
[Worker Process]
      ├── yt-dlp → download .mp4 from Instagram CDN
      ├── FFmpeg → extract audio track (.mp3)
      ├── Scrape page HTML → caption, hashtags, creator, thumbnail
      ├── OpenAI Whisper → transcription text
      ├── GPT-4o → content extraction + categorization (confidence score)
      ├── OpenAI Embeddings → vector
      ├── Store → PostgreSQL + pgvector (Supabase)
      ├── Upload thumbnail → Supabase Storage
      ├── Delete temp .mp4 + .mp3 from server
      └── FCM → Push notification to user

[Query Flow]
[ReelMind Chat UI]
      |
   HTTP POST /chat (question + category_id + user_id)
      |
[Node.js API]
      ├── Embed question → vector
      ├── pgvector similarity search → top N reels (user's saves only)
      ├── GPT-4o (RAG prompt with retrieved context) → response
      └── Return: { text, reel_cards[], sources[] }
```

